<br>
It is therefore ridiculous to ask that guilds be limited to how many rotations they can participate in because that would only be a disadvantage to the big guilds who allow the rotations to take place in the first place. Albeit that most of the big guilds are limiting their number of rotation mobs at the moment due to exploring and killing in PoP, but it is likely that will change soon when PoP mobs start going on rotation as well.<br>
<br>
There are certainly cases where bigger guilds sell tradable loot that they don't need. Guilds certainly cost alot of money to run, and it has to come from somewhere. I think the majority of this money tends to come from selling spells, particularly in SoL, but after a while, the spell market dries up and items need to be sold to fund guild activities.<br>
<br>
Rotations are certainly for the benefit of just about everyone. Our system is certainly superior to FFA where on many servers, there are 2-3 guilds all in NToV at the same time killing dragons as soon as they pop, and several guilds converging on Ssra all racing towards the named mobs. Rotations means that people don't have to waste time spawn camping a mob just for a shot of it, or arguing with another guild to see who got their first. Basically, everyone gets more time to have fun and kill the things they want and less time stressing over whether or not they will get to kill the mob they want, and waiting for it to spawn.<br>
<br>
Thun <p>Thundax Stormkeeper<br>
Warder of the Rathe<br>
